28std::unique_ptr<MediaEngineInterface> CreateMediaEngine(
29 MediaEngineDependencies dependencies) {
30 // TODO(sprang): Make populating |dependencies.trials| mandatory and remove
31 // these fallbacks.
32 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig> fallback_trials(
33 dependencies.trials ? nullptr : new webrtc::FieldTrialBasedConfig());
34 const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials =
35 dependencies.trials ? *dependencies.trials : *fallback_trials;
36 auto audio_engine = std::make_unique<WebRtcVoiceEngine>(
37 dependencies.task_queue_factory, std::move(dependencies.adm),
38 std::move(dependencies.audio_encoder_factory),
39 std::move(dependencies.audio_decoder_factory),
40 std::move(dependencies.audio_mixer),
41 std::move(dependencies.audio_processing),
42 dependencies.audio_frame_processor, trials);
43#ifdef HAVE_WEBRTC_VIDEO
44 auto video_engine = std::make_unique<WebRtcVideoEngine>(
45 std::move(dependencies.video_encoder_factory),
46 std::move(dependencies.video_decoder_factory), trials);
47#else
48 auto video_engine = std::make_unique<NullWebRtcVideoEngine>();
49#endif
50 return std::make_unique<CompositeMediaEngine>(std::move(fallback_trials),
51 std::move(audio_engine),
52 std::move(video_engine));
53}

55namespace {
56// Remove mutually exclusive extensions with lower priority.
57void DiscardRedundantExtensions(
58 std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension>* extensions,
59 rtc::ArrayView<const char* const> extensions_decreasing_prio) {
60 RTC_DCHECK(extensions);
61 bool found = false;
62 for (const char* uri : extensions_decreasing_prio) {
63 auto it = absl::c_find_if(
64 *extensions,
65 [uri](const webrtc::RtpExtension& rhs) { return rhs.uri == uri; });
66 if (it != extensions->end()) {
67 if (found) {
68 extensions->erase(it);
69 }
70 found = true;
71 }
72 }
73}
74} // namespace
75
76bool ValidateRtpExtensions(
77 const std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension>& extensions) {
78 bool id_used[1 + webrtc::RtpExtension::kMaxId] = {false};
79 for (const auto& extension : extensions) {
80 if (extension.id < webrtc::RtpExtension::kMinId ||
81 extension.id > webrtc::RtpExtension::kMaxId) {
82 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Bad RTP extension ID: " << extension.ToString();
83 return false;
84 }
85 if (id_used[extension.id]) {
86 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Duplicate RTP extension ID: "
87 << extension.ToString();
88 return false;
89 }
90 id_used[extension.id] = true;
91 }
92 return true;
93}
94
95std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension> FilterRtpExtensions(
96 const std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension>& extensions,
97 bool (*supported)(absl::string_view),
98 bool filter_redundant_extensions,
99 const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
100 RTC_DCHECK(ValidateRtpExtensions(extensions));
101 RTC_DCHECK(supported);
102 std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension> result;
103
104 // Ignore any extensions that we don't recognize.
105 for (const auto& extension : extensions) {
106 if (supported(extension.uri)) {
107 result.push_back(extension);
108 } else {
109 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unsupported RTP extension: "
110 << extension.ToString();
111 }
112 }
113
114 // Sort by name, ascending (prioritise encryption), so that we don't reset
115 // extensions if they were specified in a different order (also allows us
116 // to use std::unique below).
117 absl::c_sort(result, [](const webrtc::RtpExtension& rhs,
118 const webrtc::RtpExtension& lhs) {
119 return rhs.encrypt == lhs.encrypt ? rhs.uri < lhs.uri
120 : rhs.encrypt > lhs.encrypt;
121 });
122
123 // Remove unnecessary extensions (used on send side).
124 if (filter_redundant_extensions) {
125 auto it = std::unique(
126 result.begin(), result.end(),
127 [](const webrtc::RtpExtension& rhs, const webrtc::RtpExtension& lhs) {
128 return rhs.uri == lhs.uri && rhs.encrypt == lhs.encrypt;
129 });
130 result.erase(it, result.end());
131
132 // Keep just the highest priority extension of any in the following lists.
133 if (absl::StartsWith(trials.Lookup("WebRTC-FilterAbsSendTimeExtension"),
134 "Enabled")) {
135 static const char* const kBweExtensionPriorities[] = {
136 webrtc::RtpExtension::kTransportSequenceNumberUri,
137 webrtc::RtpExtension::kAbsSendTimeUri,
138 webrtc::RtpExtension::kTimestampOffsetUri};
139 DiscardRedundantExtensions(&result, kBweExtensionPriorities);
140 } else {
141 static const char* const kBweExtensionPriorities[] = {
142 webrtc::RtpExtension::kAbsSendTimeUri,
143 webrtc::RtpExtension::kTimestampOffsetUri};
144 DiscardRedundantExtensions(&result, kBweExtensionPriorities);
145 }
146 }
147 return result;
148}

150webrtc::BitrateConstraints GetBitrateConfigForCodec(const Codec& codec) {
151 webrtc::BitrateConstraints config;
152 int bitrate_kbps = 0;
153 if (codec.GetParam(kCodecParamMinBitrate, &bitrate_kbps) &&
154 bitrate_kbps > 0) {
155 config.min_bitrate_bps = bitrate_kbps * 1000;
156 } else {
157 config.min_bitrate_bps = 0;
158 }
159 if (codec.GetParam(kCodecParamStartBitrate, &bitrate_kbps) &&
160 bitrate_kbps > 0) {
161 config.start_bitrate_bps = bitrate_kbps * 1000;
162 } else {
163 // Do not reconfigure start bitrate unless it's specified and positive.
164 config.start_bitrate_bps = -1;
165 }
166 if (codec.GetParam(kCodecParamMaxBitrate, &bitrate_kbps) &&
167 bitrate_kbps > 0) {
168 config.max_bitrate_bps = bitrate_kbps * 1000;
169 } else {
170 config.max_bitrate_bps = -1;
171 }
172 return config;
173}
